<div id="Ovierview" class="blurbSummary grid_12">
  <div class="p">
    The topic cycle defines the process of creating one or more changesets
    related to one or more <code>issues</code>. The goal is to isolate
    in-progress changes so that when the cumalitive change comes back to the
    source
    branch<span data-perspective="detailed">&mdash;typically <code>master</code>&mdash;</span><span data-perspective="!detailed"> </span>functionality
    and correct behavior is maintained.
  </div>
</div>
<div id="Topic-Stages" class="blurbSummary grid_12">
  <div class="blurbTitle">Topic Stages</div>
  <div class="subHeader"><span>Initiating a Topic</span></div>
  <div class="p">
    A release cycle is initiated by a developer who is responsible for the
    topic changes. The actual initialization consists of issuing the <code>con
    topics start</code> command.
  </div>
  <div class="p" data-pespective="operations detail">
    The tracking branch always begins with the <code>topics-</code> prefix
    followed by one or more involved <code>issues</code>, followed by an
    optional user description. A <code>.topic-status</code> is also created to
    help manage the meta-data related to the <code>topics</code> item.
  </div>
  <div class="subHeader"><span>Development Stage</span></div>
  <div class="p">
    Develop, test, and (optionally) publish incremental changes.
  </div>
  <div class="subHeader"><span>Submitted Stage</span></div>
